Second District.

Milton Halowell, administrator, plaintiff in error, v. Chicago, Rock Island & Pacific Railway Company, defendant in error.Gen. No. 7,569.Heard in this court at the April term, 1926.Opinion filed February 21, 1927.Rehearing denied April 6, 1927.A. E. Butters and Roger H. Clark, for plaintiff in error. Woodward, Hibbs & Pool, for defendant in error; Daniel Taylor, of counsel. Mr. Justice Jones

delivered the opinion of the court.
